</br>28 For Ke´dar and the kingdoms of Ha´zor, which Neb·u·chad·rez´zar the king of Babylon struck down, this is what Jehovah has said: “Rise up, go up to Ke´dar, O men, and despoil the sons of the East.
</br>29 Their own tents and their own flocks will be taken, their tent cloths and all their articles. And their own camels will be carried off from them. And they will certainly cry out to them, ‘Fright is all around!’”
<p></p>
</br>30 “Flee, take flight far away; go down deep in order to dwell, O inhabitants of Ha´zor,” is the utterance of Jehovah. “For Neb·u·chad·rez´zar the king of Babylon has formulated a counsel even against YOU and has thought out against YOU a thought.”
